<detall><id label=""><![CDATA[103171]]></id><title label="Titol"><![CDATA[Short films created on the metro]]></title><excerpt label="Resum"><![CDATA[<strong>Films.</strong> The fifth edition of Subtravelling, the short films on the metro festival, is back, with new features and prizes.]]></excerpt><content label="Contingut"><![CDATA[<p>The fifth edition of the Subtravelling short films on the metro festival, organised by the TMB Foundation, is back in town with a vengeance, both in its new developments in the Roda TMB categories and in its prizes. Besides offering three-minute short films, this year&#8217;s event will be seeing a competition for short films of just 15 seconds. The creators of these visitors are the same people who use metro or bus public transport, those who have used their mobiles as a recording tool.</p>
<p>The short films in the Microcurts [Micro-Short] category can be seen 4 to 21 November on the festival website and on large-format screens and high-resolution projects from the MouTV users&#8217; information system. This year&#8217;s new feature is the special &#8216;Va passar a TMB&#8217; section, which celebrates the 90th anniversary of the metro in Barcelona.</p>
<p>The festival&#8217;s concluding event will be held on 25 November at the Cines Filmax Granvia, during which the winners of the various categories will be presented and the winning short films screened. In addition, there will also be draws and prizes for everyone attending.</p>
